ore he came up, we'd jump out and get underneath the bed and then he'd hit the bed because it was dark, there was no light, we used to say oh, oh, oh, you see and then when he'd gone out of the room we used to laugh. And I remember him saying to my mother
 one - one day - we were listening on the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1584246\charrsid11160377 banisters}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4792939\charrsid11160377 
